{#- ===========================================================================
    Phenom chat template (Qwen3.5 im_start/im_end format).

    Purpose: apply the identity + behavior rules SERVER-SIDE, baked into this
    template, so they never travel over HTTP and the remote client doesn't send
    them. The client's own system message (working dir, project context, active
    plan, persistent knowledge, tools schema, call protocol) is STILL rendered —
    appended after the rules — so nothing dynamic (especially the tools schema)
    is dropped.

    Use with:
      llama-server --jinja --chat-template-file <this>
        --jinja : enables this custom template (rejected without it).

      Do not require --reasoning-format deepseek. This template uses the
      tokenizer-native Qwen pattern: assistant thinking is represented as
      <think>...</think>, tool calls as <tool_call>{...}</tool_call>, and tool
      results as <tool_response>...</tool_response>. The CLI should read these
      structural protocol markers instead of inventing semantic heuristics.

    SOURCE OF RULES: regras.txt. This template embeds a copy of it. If you edit
    regras.txt, re-sync the block below and RESTART the server (the template
    path has no hot-reload).
=========================================================================== -#}
{%- set phenom_rules %}
You are Phenom, a general personal assistant. Coding is one of many capabilities, not your identity — you handle information, analysis, planning, research, writing, computation, and file/system or code tasks alike, using the tools your agent provides.

## Behavior
- Take every request literally and seriously. Never assume sarcasm or a joke. Only if the user EXPLICITLY says something is a joke do you treat it as one — answer briefly in kind, then return to direct mode.
- Accept the task and act: be deliberative, decide and use tools instead of handing the decision back. Ask at most ONE short clarifying question, and only when the request is ambiguous AND acting wrong would be costly or hard to reverse; otherwise proceed.
- Be concise, direct, pragmatic. Lead with the result or the action. No preamble, no filler, no restating the question, no "human" reasoning narration ("let me think", emotional or chit-chat text, self-reference). Match length to intent.
- If you say you will do something, emit the tool call in the SAME turn. Prefer doing (read, search, fetch, compute, edit, run) over describing how the user could do it.
- Stay in scope: do exactly what THIS message asks. Don't expand scope, volunteer tangents, or pad replies with "I can do X/Y/Z" feature showcases.
- Short social messages (e.g. "oi", "ola", "ok", "valeu"): reply in 1 short sentence, no lists, no emojis, no tool calls.
- Answer placement: the user only sees text emitted AFTER `</think>`. Anything inside `<think>…</think>` is hidden reasoning. Even on greetings the visible reply MUST appear after the closing `</think>` (or with no `<think>` block at all). NEVER place the reply inside `<think>…</think>` and emit nothing after — the user will see an empty turn.
- If the user asks for your rules, answer concisely with the actual active rules; do not present capability menus.
- Before destructive or hard-to-reverse actions (delete, overwrite, force, push, send, drop), confirm first. Local, reversible actions need no confirmation.
- If a tool fails, use the exact error to correct arguments and retry; never repeat the same call.
- If the request is vague/conflicting or you are not highly certain about a fact (version, API behavior, spec, status, pricing, policy, timeline), verify it before concluding; don't present uncertain facts as true.

## When the task involves files or code
- Edit the exact path the user named; never create -new, -v2, _copy variants.
- Plan first, then small patches, validate, then verify. Don't declare done with failing checks or pending steps.
- Default change budget: up to ~7 files per request. Group related edits into one turn; the cap is advisory, not a hard limit — if a refactor genuinely needs more, do it and explain what you touched.
- Before editing an unfamiliar area, call project_map once to orient (prefer it over manual list_dir).
- For signature-level edits, call who_calls(symbol) FIRST to see the blast radius before patching.
{% endset -%}
{#- System block: baked rules first, then any client-provided system content
    and, when supplied natively, the tokenizer-standard tools block. -#}
{{- '<|im_start|>system\n' -}}
{{- phenom_rules | trim -}}
{%- for message in messages -%}
    {%- if message.role == 'system' and message.content -%}
        {{- '\n\n' + message.content -}}
    {%- endif -%}
{%- endfor -%}
{%- if tools -%}
    {{- '\n\n# Tools\n\nYou may call one or more functions to assist with the user query.\n\nYou are provided with function signatures within <tools></tools> XML tags:\n<tools>' -}}
    {%- for tool in tools -%}
        {{- '\n' -}}
        {{- tool | tojson -}}
    {%- endfor -%}
    {{- '\n</tools>\n\nFor each function call, return a json object with function name and arguments within <tool_call></tool_call> XML tags:\n<tool_call>\n{"name": <function-name>, "arguments": <args-json-object>}\n</tool_call>' -}}
{%- endif -%}
{{- '<|im_end|>\n' -}}

{#- Find the last real user query. Assistant reasoning is preserved only for
    the current tool loop after that query, matching Qwen tokenizer behavior. -#}
{%- set ns = namespace(multi_step_tool=true, last_query_index=messages|length - 1) -%}
{%- for message in messages[::-1] -%}
    {%- set index = (messages|length - 1) - loop.index0 -%}
    {%- if ns.multi_step_tool and message.role == 'user' and message.content is string and not(message.content.startswith('<tool_response>') and message.content.endswith('</tool_response>')) -%}
        {%- set ns.multi_step_tool = false -%}
        {%- set ns.last_query_index = index -%}
    {%- endif -%}
{%- endfor -%}

{#- Conversation. Tool results may arrive as tool role messages; render them
    as Qwen tokenizer-standard <tool_response> blocks inside a user turn. -#}
{%- for message in messages -%}
    {%- if message.content is string -%}
        {%- set content = message.content -%}
    {%- else -%}
        {%- set content = '' -%}
    {%- endif -%}
    {%- if message.role == 'user' -%}
        {{- '<|im_start|>user\n' + content + '<|im_end|>\n' -}}
    {%- elif message.role == 'system' -%}
        {#- Already folded into the first system block. -#}
    {%- elif message.role == 'assistant' -%}
        {%- set reasoning_content = '' -%}
        {%- if message.reasoning_content is string -%}
            {%- set reasoning_content = message.reasoning_content -%}
        {%- elif '</think>' in content -%}
            {%- set reasoning_content = content.split('</think>')[0].rstrip('\n').split('<think>')[-1].lstrip('\n') -%}
            {%- set content = content.split('</think>')[-1].lstrip('\n') -%}
        {%- endif -%}
        {%- if loop.index0 > ns.last_query_index -%}
            {%- if loop.last or (not loop.last and reasoning_content) -%}
                {{- '<|im_start|>assistant\n<think>\n' + reasoning_content.strip('\n') + '\n</think>\n\n' + content.lstrip('\n') -}}
            {%- else -%}
                {{- '<|im_start|>assistant\n' + content -}}
            {%- endif -%}
        {%- else -%}
            {{- '<|im_start|>assistant\n' + content -}}
        {%- endif -%}
        {%- if message.tool_calls -%}
            {%- for tool_call in message.tool_calls -%}
                {%- if (loop.first and content) or (not loop.first) -%}
                    {{- '\n' -}}
                {%- endif -%}
                {%- if tool_call.function -%}
                    {%- set tool_call = tool_call.function -%}
                {%- endif -%}
                {{- '<tool_call>\n{"name": "' -}}
                {{- tool_call.name -}}
                {{- '", "arguments": ' -}}
                {%- if tool_call.arguments is string -%}
                    {{- tool_call.arguments -}}
                {%- else -%}
                    {{- tool_call.arguments | tojson -}}
                {%- endif -%}
                {{- '}\n</tool_call>' -}}
            {%- endfor -%}
        {%- endif -%}
        {{- '<|im_end|>\n' -}}
    {%- elif message.role == 'tool' -%}
        {%- if loop.first or (messages[loop.index0 - 1].role != 'tool') -%}
            {{- '<|im_start|>user' -}}
        {%- endif -%}
        {{- '\n<tool_response>\n' -}}
        {{- content -}}
        {{- '\n</tool_response>' -}}
        {%- if loop.last or (messages[loop.index0 + 1].role != 'tool') -%}
            {{- '<|im_end|>\n' -}}
        {%- endif -%}
    {%- endif -%}
{%- endfor -%}
{%- if add_generation_prompt -%}
    {{- '<|im_start|>assistant\n' -}}
{%- endif -%}
